Remote exploitation of an unspecified vulnerability in Oracle Corp.'s Java, could allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code on the targeted host.

Note: The public proof-of-concept exploit works against earlier versions of JAVA .","cve":[{"title":"CVE-2016-0636","link":"http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2016-0636"}]},"category":"Local","status":{"severity":"High","code":"Unhealthy"},"timeGenerated":"2020-08-12T20:14:15.2430000Z","remediation":"The vendor released updates (Java SE JDK and JRE 8 Update 77 or later, Java SE JDK and JRE 7 Update 99 ) to resolve these issues.

{"description":"Oracle Java Input Validation Code Execution Vulnerability (Oracle Security Alert for CVE-2016-0603)","displayName":"Oracle Java Input Validation Code Execution Vulnerability (Oracle Security Alert for CVE-2016-0603)","additionalData":{"assessedResourceType":"ServerVulnerability","type":"VirtualMachine","vendorReferences":[{"title":"Oracle Security Alert for CVE-2016-0603","link":"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/topics/security/alert-cve-2016-0603-2874360.html"}],"publishedTime":"2016-02-08T22:04:45.0000000Z","patchable":true,"cvss":{"2.0":{"base":7.6}},"threat":"Java Runtime Environment (JRE) is a platform that supports the execution of programs that are developed using the Java programming language. The JRE platform also supports Java Applets, which can be loaded from Web pages.

Remote exploitation of a input validation vulnerability in Oracle Corp.'s Java, could allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code on the targeted host.

Note : To be successfully exploited, this vulnerability requires that an unsuspecting user be tricked into visiting a malicious web site and download files into the user's system before installing Java SE 6, 7 or 8.

Affected Versions:
JDK and JRE 6 Update 111 on Windows only JDK and JRE 7 Update 95 on Windows only JDK and JRE 8 Update 71, 72 on Windows only ","cve":[{"title":"CVE-2016-0603","link":"http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2016-0603"}]},"category":"Local","status":{"severity":"High","code":"Unhealthy"},"timeGenerated":"2020-08-12T20:14:15.2430000Z","remediation":"The vendor released updates (Java SE JDK and JRE 8 Update 73 or later, Java SE JDK and JRE 7 Update 97, Java SE JDK and JRE 6 Update 113) to resolve these issues.

Refer to vendor advisory Oracle Security Alert for CVE-2016-0603 and Oracle Doc ID 2101338.1 to obtain more details.

Updates for Java 5, Java 6 and Java 7 are no longer available to the public. Oracle offers updates to Java 5 and Java 6 only for customers who have purchased Java support or have Oracle products that require Java 5, Java 6 and Java 7.","impact":"Exploitation could allow an attacker to take complete control of an affected system.","id":"124688"}

column16:
The vendor released updates (Java SE JDK and JRE 9.0.4, Java 8 Update 161 or later, Java SE JDK and JRE 7 Update 171, Java SE JDK and JRE 6 Update 181) to resolve these issues.

Refer to vendor advisory Oracle Java SE CPU January 2018 and Oracle Doc ID 2337155.1 to obtain more details.

Updates for Java 5, Java 6 and Java 7 are no longer available to the public. Oracle offers updates to Java 5, Java 6 and Java 7 only for customers who have purchased Java support or have Oracle products that require Java 5, Java 6 and Java 7.

column16:

Refer to vendor advisory Oracle Java SE CPU October 2017 and Oracle Doc ID 2305932.1 to obtain more details.
